## Schema Imports

- Never hardcode object API names or field names as strings in JS.
- Use `@salesforce/schema` imports for type safety:

```javascript
import LOYALTY_MEMBER_OBJECT from '@salesforce/schema/LoyaltyProgramMember';
import BONVOY_ID_FIELD from '@salesforce/schema/LoyaltyProgramMember.BonvoyID__c';
```

## Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component folder | `camelCase` | `loyaltyMemberCard` |
| JS class properties | `camelCase` | `memberId`, `isLoading` |
| `@api` properties | `camelCase`, descriptive | `loyaltyProgramId` |
| Custom events | `kebab-case` | `member-enrolled`, `tier-updated` |
| CSS classes | `kebab-case` | `.member-card__header` |

## HTML Template Standards

- Use `lightning-*` base components wherever possible (layout, inputs, buttons, cards, datatable).
- Avoid inline styles — use CSS classes in the component's `.css` file.
- Use `lwc:if` / `lwc:else` (API 59.0+) rather than `if:true` / `if:false` for conditional rendering.
- Keep templates lean: extract complex repeated markup into child components.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `title`, or visible label text).
- Use `lightning-button` instead of `<button>` for consistent focus management.
- Avoid removing focus outlines (`outline: none`) without providing an alternative focus indicator.

## Component Metadata (XML)

- Set `apiVersion` to match project standard (66.0).
- `isExposed: true` only for components intended to be placed on Lightning pages.
- `targets` must include only the Lightning page types where the component is actually designed to work.
- `targetConfigs` with `<supportedFormFactors>` if the component is mobile-aware.

## Performance

- Avoid loading large datasets in `connectedCallback`. Paginate or lazy-load.
- Use `lightning-datatable` with `key-field` for lists — do not build custom table rows with `template:iterator` for large datasets.
- Minimize wire calls; combine data needs into a single Apex method when multiple fields from the same record are needed.

